      "review_summary": "Adds exec outcome classification for benign `rg` no-result exits, forwards that metadata through command-output events, and renders Slack progress as `No matches found`.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for the review finding: source inspection shows exit code 1 plus an `rg` token and empty aggregate output is enough to return `benign_no_result`. I did not run tests in this read-only review, but the false-positive path is directly traceable in the proposed classifier.",
